  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 450˚F (230˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">Cut the head of cauliflower in half. Pluck bite-sized florets from each half. Trim bottoms of florets as necessary. </step>
    <step num="2">Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Spread cauliflower florets on the baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake for 20 minutes. </step>
    <step num="4">Remove florets from oven and toss with BBQ sauce. </step>
    <step num="5">Return florets to the oven and bake for an additional 10 minutes until browned to your liking. </step>
    <step num="6">Brush more BBQ sauce on the cooked cauliflower for extra flavor. </step>
    <step num="7">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
